						<summary>

						<p>On the north base of the Karivaradarāja-perumāḷ temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Kōnēriṉmaikoṇḍāṉ (Vīranārāyaṇa ?): c. 1139 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This damaged inscription records an order of the king addressed to the residents of Koḻumam granting some thing (details not preserved) to meet the expenses relating to the procession, during a festival, of the diety Karumāṇikkapirāṉ of Kumaraṅgabhīmach-chaturvēdimaṅgalam in Karaivaḻi-nāḍu.</p>						

						<p>In continuation of this record are engraved two others which also seem to be grants of land, etc., for the procession of the same deity, by some individuals. </p>						

						</summary>
